openapi: 3.0.0 info: description: Bus stop information, route and schedule data, and bus positions. title: Bus Route and Stop Methods version: "1.0" x-apisguru-categories: - transport x-logo: url: https://twitter.com/wmata/profile_image?size=original x-origin: - format: swagger url: https://developer.wmata.com/docs/services/54763629281d83086473f231/export?DocumentFormat=Swagger version: "2.0" x-providerName: wmata.com x-serviceName: bus-route security: - apiKeyHeader: [] - apiKeyQuery: [] tags: [] paths: /BusPositions: get: description: >-

Description

Returns bus positions for the given route, with an optional search radius. If no parameters are specified, all bus positions are returned.

Note that the RouteID parameter accepts only base route names and no variations, i.e.: use 10A instead of 10Av1 or 10Av2.

Bus positions are refreshed approximately every 20 to 30 7 to 10 seconds.

Response Elements

Element Description
BusPositions Array containing bus position information (BusPositions).
BusPosition Elements
DateTime Date and time (Eastern Standard Time) of last position update. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.: 2014-10-27T13:23:40).
Deviation Deviation, in minutes, from schedule. Positive values indicate that the bus is running late while negative ones are for buses running ahead of schedule.
DirectionNum Deprecated. Use the DirectionText for a customer-friendly description of direction.
DirectionText General direction of the trip, not the bus itself (e.g.: NORTH, SOUTH, EAST, WEST).
Lat Last reported Latitude of the bus.
Lon Last reported Longitude of the bus.
RouteID Base route name as shown on the bus. Note that the base route name could also refer to any variant, so a RouteID of 10A could refer to 10A, 10Av1, 10Av2, etc.
TripEndTime Scheduled end date and time (Eastern Standard Time) of the bus's current trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.: 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
TripHeadsign Destination of the bus.
TripID Unique trip ID. This can be correlated with the data returned from the schedule-related methods.
TripStartTime Scheduled start date and time (Eastern Standard Time) of the bus's current trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.: 2014-10-27T12:40:00).
VehicleID Unique identifier for the bus. This is usually visible on the bus itself.
operationId: 5476362a281d830c946a3d6e parameters: - description: "Bus route, e.g.: 70, 10A." in: query name: RouteID schema: type: string enum: - "70" default: "70" - description: Center point Latitude, required if Longitude and Radius are specified. in: query name: Lat schema: type: string - description: Center point Longitude, required if Latitude and Radius are specified. in: query name: Lon schema: type: string - description: Radius (meters) to include in the search area, required if Latitude and Longitude are specified. in: query name: Radius schema: type: string responses: "200": description: Default response code. content: application/xml: examples: response: value: >- 2014-10-27T13:23:40 7.0000000000 10 NORTH 39.191525 -76.672821 B30 2014-10-27T13:17:00 BWI LT RAIL STA 6794838 2014-10-27T12:40:00 6217 2014-10-27T13:23:19 -1.0000000000 12 SOUTH 39.030003 -76.948868 B30 2014-10-27T13:29:00 GREENBELT STA 6794867 2014-10-27T12:53:00 6215 2014-10-27T13:24:00 2.0000000000 10 NORTH 39.011429 -76.893158 B30 2014-10-27T13:57:00 BWI LT RAIL STA 6794839 2014-10-27T13:20:00 6213 summary: XML - Bus Position /RouteDetails: get: description: "

Description

\r

For a given date, returns the set of ordered latitude/longitude points along route variant along with the list of stops served.

\r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
Direction0/Direction1\r Structures describing path/stopinformation.
\r
\r Most routes will return content in both Direction0 and Direction1 elements, though a few will return NULL for Direction0 or for Direction1.
\r
\r 0 or 1 are binary properties. There is no specific mapping to direction, but a different value for the same route signifies that the route is in an opposite direction.\r
NameDescriptive name for the route.
RouteIDBus route variant (e.g.: 10A, 10Av1, etc.).
\r
\r Direction0/Direction1 Elements\r
\r
DirectionNumDeprecated. Use the DirectionText element to denote the general direction of the route variant.
DirectionTextGeneral direction of the route variant (NORTH, SOUTH, EAST, WEST, LOOP, etc.).
Shape\r Array containing shape point information (ShapePoint).\r
Stops\r Array containing stop information (Stop).\r
TripHeadsignDescriptive text of where the bus is headed. This is similar, but not necessarily identical, to what is displayed on the bus.
\r
\r ShapePoint Elements\r
\r
LatLatitude.
LonLongitude.
SeqNumOrder of the point in the sequence of ShapePoints.
\r
\r Stop Elements\r
\r
LatLatitude.
LonLongitude.
NameStop name. May be slightly different from what is spoken or displayed in the bus.
RoutesString array of route variants which provide service at this stop. Note that these are not date-specific; any route variant which stops at this stop on any day will be listed.
StopID7-digit regional ID which can be used in various bus-related methods. If unavailable, the StopID will be 0 or NULL.

GREENBELT-BWI (647) B30 summary: XML - Path Details /RouteSchedule: get: description: "

Description

\r \r

Returns schedules for a given route variant for a given date.

\r \r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
Direction0/Direction1\r Arrays containing trip information (Trip).
\r
\r Most routes will return content in both Direction0 and\r Direction1 elements, though a few (especially ones which run in\r a loop, such as the U8) will return content only for Direction0\r and NULL content for Direction1.
\r
\r 0 or 1 are binary properties. There is no specific mapping to\r direction, but a different value for the same route signifies\r that the route is in an opposite direction.\r
NameDescriptive name for the route.
\r
\r Trip Elements\r
\r
DirectionNumDeprecated. Use the\r TripDirectionText element to denote the general direction of the\r trip.
EndTimeScheduled end date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
RouteIDBus route variant. This can be used in several other bus\r methods which accept variants.
StartTimeScheduled start date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
StopTimes\r Array containing location and time information (StopTime).\r
TripDirectionTextGeneral direction of the trip (NORTH, SOUTH, EAST, WEST, LOOP,\r etc.).
TripHeadsignDescriptive text of where the bus is headed. This is similar,\r but not necessarily identical, to what is displayed on the\r bus.
TripIDUnique trip ID. This can be correlated with the data returned\r from the schedule-related methods.
\r
\r StopTime Elements\r
\r
StopID7-digit regional ID which can be used in various bus-related\r methods. If unavailable, the StopID will be 0 or NULL.
StopNameStop name. May be slightly different from what is spoken or\r displayed in the bus.
StopSeqOrder of the stop in the sequence of StopTimes.
TimeScheduled departure date and time (Eastern Standard Time) from\r this stop. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).

3003037 GREENBELT STATION + BUS BAY D 82 2014-10-27T23:19:00 SOUTH GREENBELT STATION 6794856 B30 - B30 GREENBELT-BWI (647) summary: XML - Schedule /Routes: get: description: "

Description

\r \r

Returns a list of all bus route variants (patterns). For example, the 10A\r and 10Av1 are the same route, but may stop at slightly different locations.

\r \r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
Routes\r Array containing route variant information (Route).\r
\r
\r Route Elements\r
\r
NameDescriptive name of the route variant.
RouteIDUnique identifier for a given route variant. Can be used in\r various other bus-related methods.
LineDescriptionDenotes the route variants grouping lines are a combination of routes which lie in the same corridor and which have significant portions of their paths along the same roadways.
" operationId: 5476362a281d830c946a3d70 responses: "200": description: Default response code. content: application/xml: examples: response: value: >- Hunting Point-Pentagon Line 10A - HUNTING POINT -PENTAGON 10A Hunting Point-Pentagon Line 10A - PENDELTON+COLUMBUS-PENTAGON 10Av1 Hunting Point-Ballston Line 10B - HUNTING POINT - BALLSTON STA 10B Hunting Point-Ballston Line 10B - BALLSTON STA - PENDLETON+COLUMBS 10Bc summary: XML - Routes /StopSchedule: get: description: "

Description

\r \r

Returns a set of buses scheduled at a stop for a given date.

\r \r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
ScheduleArrivals\r Array containing scheduled arrival information (ScheduleArrival).\r
Stop\r Structure describing stop information.\r
\r
\r ScheduleArrival Elements\r
\r
DirectionNumDenotes a binary direction (0 or 1) of the bus. There is no\r specific mapping to direction, but a different value for the same\r route signifies that the buses are traveling in opposite\r directions. Use the TripDirectionText element to show the actual\r destination of the bus.
EndTimeScheduled end date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
RouteIDBus route variant identifier (pattern). This variant can be\r used in several other bus methods which accept variants. Note that\r customers will never see anything other than the base route name,\r so variants 10A, 10Av1, 10Av2, etc. will be displayed as 10A on the\r bus.
ScheduleTimeDate and time (Eastern Standard Time) when the bus is scheduled\r to stop at this location. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format\r (e.g.: 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
StartTimeScheduled start date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
TripDirectionTextGeneral direction of the trip (e.g.: NORTH, SOUTH, EAST,\r WEST).
TripHeadsignDestination of the bus.
TripIDTrip identifier. This can be correlated with the data in our\r bus schedule information as well as bus positions.
\r
\r Stop Elements\r
\r
LatLatitude.
LonLongitude.
NameStop name. May be slightly different from what is spoken or\r displayed in the bus.
RoutesString array of route variants which provide service at this\r stop. Note that these are not date-specific; any route variant\r which stops at this stop on any day will be listed.
StopID7-digit regional ID which can be used in various bus-related\r methods. If unavailable, the StopID will be 0 or NULL.
" operationId: 5476362a281d830c946a3d72 parameters: - description: 7-digit regional stop ID. in: query name: StopID required: true schema: type: string enum: - "1001195" default: "1001195" - description: Date in YYYY-MM-DD format for which to retrieve schedule. Description

Returns bus positions for the given route, with an optional search radius. If no parameters are specified, all bus positions are returned.

Note that the RouteID parameter accepts only base route names and no variations, i.e.: use 10A instead of 10Av1 or 10Av2.

Bus positions are refreshed approximately every 20 to 30 7 to 10 seconds.

Response Elements

Element Description
BusPositions Array containing bus position information (BusPositions).
BusPosition Elements
DateTime Date and time (Eastern Standard Time) of last position update. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.: 2014-10-27T13:23:40).
Deviation Deviation, in minutes, from schedule. Positive values indicate that the bus is running late while negative ones are for buses running ahead of schedule.
DirectionNum Deprecated. Use the DirectionText for a customer-friendly description of direction.
DirectionText General direction of the trip, not the bus itself (e.g.: NORTH, SOUTH, EAST, WEST).
Lat Last reported Latitude of the bus.
Lon Last reported Longitude of the bus.
RouteID Base route name as shown on the bus. Note that the base route name could also refer to any variant, so a RouteID of 10A could refer to 10A, 10Av1, 10Av2, etc.
TripEndTime Scheduled end date and time (Eastern Standard Time) of the bus's current trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.: 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
TripHeadsign Destination of the bus.
TripID Unique trip ID. This can be correlated with the data returned from the schedule-related methods.
TripStartTime Scheduled start date and time (Eastern Standard Time) of the bus's current trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.: 2014-10-27T12:40:00).
VehicleID Unique identifier for the bus. This is usually visible on the bus itself.

Description

\r \r

For a given date, returns the set of ordered latitude/longitude points along\r a route variant along with the list of stops served.

\r \r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
Direction0/Direction1\r Structures describing path/stop\r information.
\r
\r Most routes will return content in both Direction0 and\r Direction1 elements, though a few will return NULL for Direction0 or for Direction1.
\r
\r 0 or 1 are binary properties. There is no specific mapping to\r direction, but a different value for the same route signifies\r that the route is in an opposite direction.\r
NameDescriptive name for the route.
RouteIDBus route variant (e.g.: 10A, 10Av1, etc.).
\r
\r Direction0/Direction1\r Elements\r
\r
DirectionNumDeprecated. Use the\r DirectionText element to denote the general direction of the route\r variant.
DirectionTextGeneral direction of the route variant (NORTH, SOUTH, EAST,\r WEST, LOOP, etc.).
Shape\r Array containing shape point information (ShapePoint).\r
Stops\r Array containing stop information (Stop).\r
TripHeadsignDescriptive text of where the bus is headed. This is similar,\r but not necessarily identical, to what is displayed on the\r bus.
\r
\r ShapePoint\r Elements\r
\r
LatLatitude.
LonLongitude.
SeqNumOrder of the point in the sequence of ShapePoints.
\r
\r Stop Elements\r
\r
LatLatitude.
LonLongitude.
NameStop name. May be slightly different from what is spoken or\r displayed in the bus.
RoutesString array of route variants which provide service at this\r stop. Note that these are not date-specific; any route variant\r which stops at this stop on any day will be listed.
StopID7-digit regional ID which can be used in various bus-related\r methods. If unavailable, the StopID will be 0 or NULL.

NameDescriptive name for the route.
\r
\r Trip Elements\r
\r
DirectionNumDeprecated. Use the\r TripDirectionText element to denote the general direction of the\r trip.
EndTimeScheduled end date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
RouteIDBus route variant. This can be used in several other bus\r methods which accept variants.
StartTimeScheduled start date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
StopTimes\r Array containing location and time information (StopTime).\r
TripDirectionTextGeneral direction of the trip (NORTH, SOUTH, EAST, WEST, LOOP,\r etc.).
TripHeadsignDescriptive text of where the bus is headed. This is similar,\r but not necessarily identical, to what is displayed on the\r bus.
TripIDUnique trip ID. This can be correlated with the data returned\r from the schedule-related methods.
\r
\r StopTime Elements\r
\r
StopID7-digit regional ID which can be used in various bus-related\r methods. If unavailable, the StopID will be 0 or NULL.
StopNameStop name. May be slightly different from what is spoken or\r displayed in the bus.
StopSeqOrder of the stop in the sequence of StopTimes.
TimeScheduled departure date and time (Eastern Standard Time) from\r this stop. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).

B30 GREENBELT-BWI (647) summary: JSON - Schedule /json/jRoutes: get: description: "

Description

\r \r

Returns a list of all bus route variants (patterns). For example, the 10A\r and 10Av1 are the same route, but may stop at slightly different locations.

\r \r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
Routes\r Array containing route variant information (Route).\r
\r
\r Route Elements\r
\r
NameDescriptive name of the route variant.
RouteIDUnique identifier for a given route variant. Can be used in\r various other bus-related methods.
LineDescriptionDenotes the route variants grouping lines are a combination of routes which lie in the same corridor and which have significant portions of their paths along the same roadways.
" operationId: 5476362a281d830c946a3d6a responses: "200": description: Default response type. content: application/json: examples: response: value: Routes: - LineDescription: Hunting Point-Pentagon Line Name: 10A - HUNTING POINT -PENTAGON RouteID: 10A - LineDescription: Hunting Point-Pentagon Line Name: 10A - PENDELTON+COLUMBUS-PENTAGON RouteID: 10Av1 - LineDescription: Hunting Point-Ballston Line Name: 10B - HUNTING POINT - BALLSTON STA RouteID: 10B - LineDescription: Hunting Point-Ballston Line Name: 10B - BALLSTON STA - PENDLETON+COLUMBS RouteID: 10Bc summary: JSON - Routes /json/jStopSchedule: get: description: "

Description

\r \r

Returns a set of buses scheduled at a stop for a given date.

\r \r

Response Elements

\r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r \r
ElementDescription
ScheduleArrivals\r Array containing scheduled arrival information (ScheduleArrival).\r
Stop\r Structure describing stop information.\r
\r
\r ScheduleArrival Elements\r
\r
DirectionNumDenotes a binary direction (0 or 1) of the bus. There is no\r specific mapping to direction, but a different value for the same\r route signifies that the buses are traveling in opposite\r directions. Use the TripDirectionText element to show the actual\r destination of the bus.
EndTimeScheduled end date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
RouteIDBus route variant identifier (pattern). This variant can be\r used in several other bus methods which accept variants. Note that\r customers will never see anything other than the base route name,\r so variants 10A, 10Av1, 10Av2, etc. will be displayed as 10A on the\r bus.
ScheduleTimeDate and time (Eastern Standard Time) when the bus is scheduled\r to stop at this location. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format\r (e.g.: 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
StartTimeScheduled start date and time (Eastern Standard Time) for this\r trip. Will be in YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ss format (e.g.:\r 2014-10-27T13:17:00).
TripDirectionTextGeneral direction of the trip (e.g.: NORTH, SOUTH, EAST,\r WEST).
TripHeadsignDestination of the bus.
TripIDTrip identifier. This can be correlated with the data in our\r bus schedule information as well as bus positions.
\r
\r Stop Elements\r
\r
LatLatitude.
LonLongitude.
NameStop name. May be slightly different from what is spoken or\r displayed in the bus.
RoutesString array of route variants which provide service at this\r stop. Note that these are not date-specific; any route variant\r which stops at this stop on any day will be listed.
StopID7-digit regional ID which can be used in various bus-related\r methods. If unavailable, the StopID will be 0 or NULL.
